column10:
Probably one of the best games I've ever played - can't say too many games out there ever had me thinking about the world and story line in-depth even when I wasn't playing the game; 

I don't have a top-tier rig, so there were the expected issues with FPS, game dynamics, clipping, and the occasional crash; Didn't really matter though; The story line is compelling enough to look past those issues, and overall the graphics and game play were mostly smooth; 

Phantom Liberty dropped during my first play thru - I added it right before playing the final missions of the original's main story line; This was a good call because it extended my first run by 20-30 hrs; But I'll also say I didn't really find the PL content and story all that mind-blowing compared to the main game - the 'spy'-thriller angle just didn't seem to fit the world (or maybe it was just not executed properly? idk); Fortunately, I still had the main game's final, face-melting missions, which allowed me to look on PL as sort of a long side quest that just wasn't that interesting; 

So only negative: PL didn't live up to the rest of the CP2077 world imo; Whatever tho, countdowns on to CP:Orion - hopefully won't take another 10 years...
